text: Bolesław Dubicki (16 September 1934 – 15 February 2004) was a Polish wrestler. He competed at the 1960 Summer Olympics and the 1964 Summer Olympics. He was born in Warsaw. Dubicki died on 15 February 2004 in Warsaw at the age of 69.Bolesław Dubicki == References == Category:1934 births Category:2004 deaths Category:Polish wrestlers Category:Olympians for Poland Category:Sportspeople from Warsaw
